<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
          xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:ns3="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
          xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
          version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="kalman_predict" xml:lang="en">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>kalman_predict</refname>
        <refpurpose>Perform Kalman filter prediction step</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Syntax</title>
        <synopsis>
            [x_pred, P_pred] = kalman_predict(x, P, F, Q)
            gs_pred = kalman_predict(gs, F, Q)
        </synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Arguments</title>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>x</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Column vector (n x 1), current state estimate</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>P</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Matrix (n x n), current state covariance</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>gs</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>GaussianState struct, current Gaussian state</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>F</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Matrix (n x n), state transition matrix</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>Q</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Matrix (n x n), process noise covariance</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>x_pred</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Column vector (n x 1), predicted state</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>P_pred</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Matrix (n x n), predicted covariance</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>gs_pred</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>GaussianState struct, predicted Gaussian state</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            <literal>kalman_predict</literal> performs the prediction step of the Kalman filter,
            propagating the state estimate forward in time using the state transition model.
        </para>
        <para>
            The prediction equations are:
        </para>
        <programlisting><![CDATA[
x_pred = F * x
P_pred = F * P * F' + Q
        ]]></programlisting>
        <para>
            where:
        </para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem><para>F is the state transition matrix</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Q is the process noise covariance</para></listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
// Constant velocity model in 1D
// State: [position; velocity]
x = [0; 10];  // at origin, moving at 10 units/sec
P = [1, 0; 0, 1];  // initial uncertainty

dt = 0.1;  // time step
F = [1, dt; 0, 1];  // constant velocity transition
Q = [0.01, 0; 0, 0.01];  // small process noise

// Predict to next time step
[x_pred, P_pred] = kalman_predict(x, P, F, Q);
disp("Predicted position: " + string(x_pred(1)));
disp("Predicted velocity: " + string(x_pred(2)));

// Using GaussianState
gs = GaussianState(x, P);
gs_pred = kalman_predict(gs, F, Q);
        ]]></programlisting>
    </refsection>
